article.description: Carlos Johnson had a career-high 31 points as Grand Canyon beat Seattle 84-75 in the quarterfinals of the Western Athletic Conference Tournament on Thursday night.
article.headline: Johnson scores 31, Grand Canyon tops Seattle 84-75 in WAC
article.linkText: Johnson scores 31, Grand Canyon tops Seattle 84-75 in WAC
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Carlos Johnson had a career-high 31 points as Grand Canyon beat Seattle 84-75 in the quarterfinals of the Western Athletic Conference Tournament on Thursday night. Michael Finke had 21 points for Grand Canyon (19-12). Alessandro Lever added 12 points. Trey Drechsel had seven rebounds for Grand Canyon. Terrell Brown had 23 points and seven rebounds for the Redhawks (18-14). Morgan Means added 22 points.
